^b@2^*bVertical Position^*n

You can set the current vertical position (where, up or down the page the next line of text will appear) by using a two letter pair 'bar command'.  Unfortunately this command has about the worst name possible.

^c!^*bht^*n!<letter>!    @-   think        ^*bH^*nell of a silly name for vertical ^*bT^*next position         (or whatever)   [sigh]

<letter> is  a to z,  or  A to Z.  Every page is divided up into 25 zones (not the same as the height of a line) the top of the page is at zone 'a' and zone 'z' is little up from the bottom of the page.   (26 letters, 25 zones).





